Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at Schriever Air Force Base in Colorado Springs, Colorado, expressing gratitude and support for the men and women serving in the United States Armed Forces. Pence highlighted the importance of space and cyberspace operations in national security, and praised the work being done at Schriever Air Force Base. He also announced that President Donald Trump will be relaunching the National Space Council and that Pence will serve as its chairman. Pence emphasized the administration's commitment to rebuilding the military and increasing military spending, as well as improving healthcare for veterans. He concluded his speech by expressing his gratitude to the servicemen and servicewomen and assuring them of the support and prayers of the American people.